glfw
------------------------------------------
GLFW is a free, Open Source, multi-platform library for OpenGL and OpenGL ES
application development. It provides a simple, platform-independent API for
creating windows and contexts, reading input, handling events, etc.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  cygwin-devel-1.7.35-1
  libGL-devel-10.3.7-1
  libGL1-10.3.7-1
  libglfw-devel-3.1.1-1bl1
  libglfw3-3.1.1-1bl1
  libX11-devel-1.6.3-1
  libX11_6-1.6.3-1
  libXcursor-devel-1.1.14-1
  libXcursor1-1.1.14-1
  libXi-devel-1.7.4-1
  libXi6-1.7.4-1
  libXinerama-devel-1.1.3-1
  libXinerama1-1.1.3-1
  libXrandr-devel-1.4.2-1
  libXrandr2-1.4.2-1
  libXxf86vm-devel-1.1.3-1bl2
  libXxf86vm1-1.1.3-1bl2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.25-1
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-objc-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/glfw/glfw

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/glfw/glfw/archive/3.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack glfw-3.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./glfw-3.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glfw-3.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/glfw-3.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglfw3-3.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglfw-devel-3.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(glfw)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/glfw.README
  /usr/share/doc/glfw/COPYING.txt
  /usr/share/doc/glfw/README.md

(libglfw3)
  /usr/bin/cygglfw-3.dll

(libglfw-devel)
  /usr/include/GLFW/glfw3.h
  /usr/include/GLFW/glfw3native.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfw3Config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfw3ConfigVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfwTargets-relwithdebinfo.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/glfw/glfwTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libglfw.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/glfw3.pc

